   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter" part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_unknown_02_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#1-North-Audley-Street_ENK"
                             instant="false"
                             full="yes">1 North Audley Street</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  Monday Eve<hi rend="superscript">[unclear]n[/unclear]</hi>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p part="N">Dear Sir I am much obliged<lb/> 
                  to you for Puss - a most elegant<lb/>
            Dandy he is -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">Since I saw you <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsX1" instant="false" full="yes">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Wilson</persName> has<lb/>
               seen <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DaviJ1" instant="false" full="yes">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Davis</persName> the gentleman<lb/>
            who has written the best books<lb/>
               we have on <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#CN" instant="false" full="yes">China</placeName> - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DaviJ1" instant="false" full="yes">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <choice>
                     <orig>D</orig>
                     <reg instant="false">Davis</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> says<lb/>
               that his history of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#CN" instant="false" full="yes">China</placeName> has been<lb/>
            translated into French; but<lb/>
               he has written <title ref="./Workography.xml#Sketch2">"<hi rend="underline">sketches of China</hi>"</title>
               <lb/>
            which as far as he knows<lb/>
            have not been translated -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">I wish you would be so good<lb/>
                  to send to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParkE1" instant="false" full="yes">Madame Belloc</persName> a<lb/>
               copy of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DaviJ1" instant="false" full="yes">Davis</persName>'s <title ref="./Workography.xml#Sketch2">Sketches of China</title>
               <lb/>
               (published by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#KnigC1" instant="false" full="yes">Knight</persName>) You have<lb/>
            means probably of conveying<lb/>
            the book to her more <choice>
                  <orig>expedi-<lb/>
               tiously</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">expeditiously</reg>
               </choice> to her than I could -<lb/>
            and you know that expedition<lb/>
            is more than half the battle<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_unknown_02_page02.jpg"/>
            
            in these cases -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">I am not quite ready<lb/>
            yet to talk to you about my<lb/>
            own affairs - When I am I<lb/>
            will write to you again</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
                     Meanwhile I am<lb/>
                     Yours truly - obliged<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1" instant="false" full="yes">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p part="N">
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParkE1" instant="false" full="yes">Madame <choice>
                        <orig>Bellocs</orig>
                        <reg instant="false">Belloc's</reg>
                     </choice>
                  </persName> [unclear]address[/unclear] of<lb/>
                  course you know but<lb/> 
                  I can do no harm by<lb/>
                  adding it here -<lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Rue-de-Medicine-5_FR"
                             instant="false"
                             full="yes">Rue de l'Ecole de Medicine<lb/>
                     N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 5</placeName>
               </p>
               <lb/>
            </postscript>
